Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: peek
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Process intelligence tool for Linux
 peek is a single, unified CLI tool that explains what a Linux process is,
 what it is doing, how it is consuming system resources, and gives intelligent
 options to act on that knowledge — all in plain English.
 .
 Features: live TUI dashboard, resource sparklines, kernel context, network
 inspector, open file listing, environment variable redaction (secrets auto-
 hidden), process tree, signal impact pre-flight analysis, systemd integration,
 and JSON/HTML/Markdown/PDF export.

Package: peekd
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: peek (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Background daemon for peek resource history and alerting
 peekd is the optional background daemon for the peek process intelligence
 tool. It samples watched processes every second into a ring buffer, exposes
 a Unix socket for peek --history queries, and fires configurable threshold
 alerts for CPU, memory, FD count, and thread count.

